So we had a big mako craze at the beginning of this project, but I think in general we all found it to be fairly un-intuitive and difficult to work with. I'm hesitant to think that adding more mako is the way to go here. High level, we have 5-6 dump types right? Do we really need this type of change to support that (vs. just hard coding them)?

The problem is we have to support OpenPOWER specific dumps, Are there any good alternative ways to expand the dump types to support extended dumps?
here is the commit adding OpenPOWER dump types
https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-debug-collector/+/65047
